鰔字的基本解释

鰔
jiān
古书上说的一种鱼，形状像银鱼，嘴像针。

鰔字的汉语字典释义

[①]［jiān］
［《集韻》居咸切，平咸，見。］
鱼名。状如银鱼。

鰔字的康熙字典解释

【亥集中】【魚字部】　鰔； 康熙笔画：20； 页码：页1475第09
【集韻】古?切，音感。與鱤同。魚名。魠也。一曰黃頰。又【集韻】居咸切，音緘。又胡讒切，音咸。又古咸切，音緘。又古斬切，音減。義?同。

Basic explanation of words
鰔
jiān
A kind of fish mentioned in ancient books, shaped like a silver fish, with a mouth like a needle.
鰔
Chinese dictionary definition of words
[①]［jiān］
["Jiyun" in Xianqie, Pingxian, see you. ]
The name of the fish. Shaped like a whitebait.
鰔
Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words
[Hai Collection] [Fish Character Department] 　鰔; Kangxi Strokes: 20; Page Number: Page 1475 Page 09
[Jiyun] Ancient? Cut, sound sense. Same as 鱤. The name of the fish.魠 also. One said yellow cheeks. Also 【Jiyun】Has a salty cut, the sound is silent. It is slanderous and cut, and the sound is salty. The ancient salty cut, the sound is silent. Gu cut and cut again, the sound is reduced. Righteous? Same.
